Apostibes afghana is a moth of the family Scythrididae. It was described by Pietro Passerin d'Entr√®ves and Angela Roggero in 2003. It is found in north-eastern Afghanistan.
The length of the forewings is 12-13.5 mm. The forewings are whitish, slightly striped by light brown. The hindwings are white with a metallic hue, and a darker fringe.